Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:04.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones who shrunk my body, the Black Organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.90,0:00:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With each move I've made toward grasping the Organization's weakness thus far...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.77,0:00:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The FBI has been a figure that supported me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.15,0:00:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We successfully put Kir—Mizunashi Rena—in as a thread connecting us to the Organization, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.33,0:00:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a dangerous gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president of Foreign Talent Productions was killed at the New Beika Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspects are...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:31.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Irina Palm (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.46,0:00:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The secretary, Irina Palmer{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:33.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hal Buckner (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An English teacher, Hal Buckner{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.13,0:00:36.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toby Keynes (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.59,0:00:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A model, Toby Keynes{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:39.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Andre Camel (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And surprisingly, the FBI agent, Andre Camel{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the fourth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The memo the president Sunouchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wrote as he was dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The memo we believe the culprit took away, said this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:51.53,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jodie Starling\NFBI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.90,0:00:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Bring my tux."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.82,0:00:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watashi no tuxedo tottekite kure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could this dying message have meant?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, the FBI agent Akai received a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akai Shuuichi\NFBI
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.66,0:01:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.62,0:01:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.54,0:01:10.80,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mizunashi Rena / Hondou Hidemi\NCIA
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.54,0:01:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's become difficult to stay in the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.29,0:01:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want your help to leave and fly out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll mail you the time and place after this call.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.51,0:01:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.89,0:01:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was Mizunashi Rena on the phone, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.10,0:01:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She asked if we could meet now in private.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A private meeting with her could be a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.82,0:01:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would me more prudent not to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.24,0:01:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it is a trap and I do not show, in 7 or 8 cases out of 9, she'll be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Organization must have forced her do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.83,0:01:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.17,0:01:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm confident my sixth sense will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She may just be CIA...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.97,0:01:58.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I believe she has a clever plan to get out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.76,0:02:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, I'll call Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} so we can...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.06,0:02:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tingling suspense is building.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.96,0:02:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running in the darkness —\ha red scream and a black shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Detective Boys burst into spontaneous laughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A magic word identifies the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.25,0:04:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan is brought to you by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:13.94,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,CLASH OF RED AND BLACK\NREADY TO DIE
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.98,0:04:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what the report from Chiba said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.65,0:04:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to our investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the mail from the president to his secretary, Irina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was in English because she can't read or write Japanese well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:24.49,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Irina Palmer (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:32.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hal Buckner (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hal{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really is working as an English teacher in a nearby cram school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.00,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toby Keynes (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toby{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} truly is working as a model for fashion magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've confirmed all of that to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Camel{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:45.68,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Andre Camel (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We believe he is with the FBI since fellow agent Jodie attests to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:49.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we ask that you please wait a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.18,0:04:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you solved the mystery behind that memo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.27,0:04:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to say we're still looking into that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Memo"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the "dining message," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not how you say it, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.11,0:05:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's "dying message."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.70,0:05:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we're just waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really need to leave in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.37,0:05:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The class I'm in charge of starts very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I please go to the hotel reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to cancel many appointments...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.84,0:05:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we may find out about the people the president met today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it won't be a problem if they're accompanied by a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:39.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Hal{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you'll have to give up your lesson for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to tell the principal the reason for my absence in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.82,0:05:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cram school's really close, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.66,0:05:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You escort Irina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have him take Hal{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:05:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone was just killed here...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're worried about lessons and parties?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.63,0:06:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's some nerve, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.47,0:06:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the culprit took the memo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.98,0:06:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought Shuu might know the meaning of that tuxedo memo, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't reach him because my cellphone hasn't been working right since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.24,0:06:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just borrow my cellphone for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't your friends' messages and phone numbers inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I cleared all of my mail data recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.42,0:06:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if I remove my cellphone's sim card, you won't be able to see the phone numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we insert your sim card into my phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be just like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have the same type of phone, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.85,0:06:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won't it be a problem if you don't have a cellphone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.23,0:07:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll use it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.69,0:07:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that's strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They have different shapes outside, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.16,0:07:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the inside, they're the cellphones we're used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.25,0:07:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like how Camel{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is really-with the FBI inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't judge him just by his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.26,0:07:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of you I figured out the mystery of the memo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:39.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to interrupt your excitement, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you explain it simply so I can understand it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A perfect spell to reveal the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a single shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It reveals the culprit when you cast it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does require some preparations, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Preparations?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we'll need a chair for each person...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.54,0:08:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's simple, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will this really reveal the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It definitely should, since I heard about this spell from Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said so, maybe it will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "a spell that will reveal the culprit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.56,0:08:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.24,0:08:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In front of the suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.78,0:08:38.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're such an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.74,0:08:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If culprits could be identified like this, we'd no longer need the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I figured they'd say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.13,0:08:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you really going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us without the jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm serious about what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.51,0:08:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:08:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please provide four chairs for the suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, for an interrogation, wouldn't it be best to take them to the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's to find out who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should know if we do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will it really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:19.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.67,0:09:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight at 19:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seventh left curve along the Raiha Pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that pass so late, there would be few cars passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be the ideal place for a clandestine meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this really all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.65,0:09:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have some faith in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, of course, in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.45,0:10:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.46,0:10:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.54,0:10:08.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for what happens afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, all four of our suspects need to stand in front of the chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are we going to be doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.25,0:10:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am afraid...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be more effective to question us individually?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's do as the inspector says.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.35,0:11:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like playing a "mystery game."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:08.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sit down yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.64,0:11:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he really going to say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.27,0:11:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.23,0:11:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would just laugh if he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you're all four gathered there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiranpuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.77,0:12:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why did you all sit down?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the inspector just said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit down, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For foreigners who are used to hearing English, "shiranpuri" sounds like...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sit down, please."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.10,0:12:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is especially true if they're already standing in front of chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, even though you appear to be a foreigner...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.69,0:12:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're actually Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, since your ears are not accustomed to hearing English, you could only understand the original meaning: "Play innocent"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agent Jodie?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.92,0:13:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.25,0:13:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.92,0:13:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case went like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:08.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shooting victim was the president of a foreign talent company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the president was meeting today with a new foreign talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.35,0:13:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also due the police's quick arrival, there were four suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first is the secretary, Irina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we have the foreigners who were in the hotel at the time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English teacher, Hal Buckner{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The model, Toby Keynes{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then we have the one who was training on the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.04,0:13:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,FBI agent Andre Camel, which makes four.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clue was a blank memo pad on the president's desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the president's blood on his hand, the pen, and the edges of the memo pad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We surmised that the culprit made off with the memo that the president wrote as he was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Analysis showed that the traces left by the pen on the paper said, "Bring my tux."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That meant, "bring my tuxedo."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.78,0:14:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to what the secretary Irina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had planned to go out to a party tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.36,0:14:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the memo was likely a message the president wrote himself for his secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You understand now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-So, why...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the culprit take such an ordinary memo?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.29,0:14:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he couldn't read the English!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit didn't know what it meant, so he got scared and ran off with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.93,0:14:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, after shooting the president, the criminal was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking around for something and noticed the dead president was holding the pen and the memo pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.77,0:14:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit thought he had written about him and took it as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, actually, the president had already stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That memo was just a message for his secretary, written in English so she could understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the cram school English teacher, Hal Buckner{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The secretary that exchanged messages with him only in English, Irina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.42,0:15:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the FBI agent Camel{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are all eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That leaves us with the one most likely to take the memo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who likely cannot read English...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.76,0:15:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toby Keynes{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it has to be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Where's the proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't going to accuse me of being the culprit simply because I don't know English, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.53,0:15:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what would you all do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.28,0:15:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you picked up a piece of paper with something bad about you written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would probably just throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:43.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.50,0:15:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want to read it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what if it were written in a code you didn't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't throw it away, in that case;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would want to know what it said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.30,0:15:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd take it with me and try really hard to figure it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the culprit probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let me check something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.53,0:16:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to take it home and ask my American girlfriend's younger brother what it said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:25.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.29,0:16:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.21,0:16:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was overworked by that president, so much that her health suffered and at the end of last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't even listen to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Overworked"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.06,0:16:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made her sign a contract written in Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She could speak a few words of Japanese...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she couldn't read at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.07,0:16:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, in case she were unable to work...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:57.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contract made her brother responsible for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.66,0:17:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to at least save her brother, I decided to threaten him at gunpoint to get back that contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made him scout me out in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.92,0:17:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he said the contract wasn't in the room and he'd have to get his secretary to bring it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pulled the trigger without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.43,0:17:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the file the president asked me to get...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.02,0:17:24.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her contract should be somewhere inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had known his secretary were such a slender lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.36,0:17:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But "shiranpuri" was a really nice one...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.91,0:17:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know that I can't speak English and am really Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Reception."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was "reception."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.96,0:17:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the secretary left saying she was going to the hotel's reception...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say, Toby{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone was just killed here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.89,0:18:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're worried about lessons and parties?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.10,0:18:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's some nerve, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For foreigners, a hotel's "reception" is what we Japanese call the "hotel front desk."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how I knew you couldn't speak English.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.78,0:18:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, she meant the front desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it sounded strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I knew it would come to this, I'd have learned more English from my American father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing my father taught me was how to fire a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How to fire a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was with the United States Forces Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although he didn't want to, when we traveled to Guam...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pleaded with him until he finally did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he planned to teach me, he should have included...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What it feels like...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To shoot someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's something I never wish to go through again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With each pull of the trigger, a bit more of your soul fades away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a horrible feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.13,0:19:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Dad and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.09,0:19:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They should have been back by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.93,0:19:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two of them will have to go without dinner tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.14,0:19:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,New York?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:33.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's right, back then, that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long hair, Japanese...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gun!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't move...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.55,0:20:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hurry up! Jump in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must be the serial killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.14,0:20:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi is still in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.61,0:20:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wai...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just asked, "Are you Japanese"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen a suspicious man?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Japanese man, unshaven, with long, silver-dyed hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't seen anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, this place is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.39,0:20:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a right at that corner to get to a main street.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can pick up a taxi from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, my friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm waiting for my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:20:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a high school student my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.02,0:21:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll suggest this once more to you and your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.78,0:21:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave this area immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was with the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, that other time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're crying again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.52,0:21:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always seem to be crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.90,0:21:40.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.07,0:21:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just remind me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.49,0:21:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of a woman who looked a lot like you.
